Result: false  
Justification:  
The condition C11 requires that for every minimal semantic basis of the claim, there exists at least one P-type argument whose justification contains that basis. Here, the claim is "Scott has a chromosomal abnormality." The P-type arguments provide contradictory conclusions: one argues for the abnormality, the other against it. Their justifications do not semantically subsume all support arguments' justifications in a way that covers all minimal bases for the claim. Specifically, the support arguments present fragmented reasoning that is not fully contained within either P argument's justification, failing to satisfy the subset requirement for every minimal basis. Thus, C11 is not satisfied.